The guide covers everything in one place. Structure is:

Script 1 (options_trader.py) — what to download, how to run, what comes out, what to do with it
Script 2 (options_monitor.py) — when exactly to run it (post-close vs intraday), what each Action means, expiry day rule
Script 3 (options_tradelog.py) — interactive close flow, what the three Excel sheets contain
Weekly routine — the full Monday-to-expiry sequence in plain steps
File reference — which files to never touch, which are auto-maintained, which need manual action
Common issues — the errors you're most likely to hit and how to fix them

================================================================================
  NSE OPTIONS TRADING SYSTEM — EXECUTION GUIDE
  Scripts: options_trader.py | options_monitor.py | options_tradelog.py
================================================================================

PREREQUISITES
─────────────
1. Python installed (3.10 or higher)
2. Dependencies installed — run once:
     pip install pandas openpyxl python-dateutil

3. All files in the same folder:
     options_trader.py
     options_monitor.py
     options_tradelog.py
     etf_rankings.xlsx         ← from your ETF momentum system
     holdings_log.json         ← from your ETF momentum system

4. Run your ETF script first each week to keep etf_rankings.xlsx and
   holdings_log.json current before running any options script.


================================================================================
SCRIPT 1 — options_trader.py
PURPOSE  : Generates new buy signals for the week
RUN WHEN : Every Monday or Friday (pick one day and stick to it)
================================================================================

STEP 1 — Download option chain CSVs from NSE
─────────────────────────────────────────────
  URL  : https://www.nseindia.com/option-chain
  How  :
    a. Select index from dropdown (start with NIFTY and BANKNIFTY)
    b. Select expiry date — download TWO files per index:
         - Nearest weekly expiry (e.g. 20-Mar-2026)
         - Next monthly expiry  (e.g. 27-Mar-2026)
    c. Click the CSV download button (top-right of the options table)
    d. Move downloaded files into your options folder — DO NOT rename them
       NSE names them automatically: option-chain-ED-NIFTY-27-Mar-2026.csv

  Indices to download (as your ETF system starts covering more sectors):
    NIFTY        → when top sector is GOLD, METAL, ENERGY, IT, HEALTHCARE etc.
    BANKNIFTY    → when top sector is PRIVATE_BANK, PSU_BANK, BANKING_BROAD
    FINNIFTY     → when top sector is FACTOR_VALUE or FINANCIAL
    MIDCPNIFTY   → when top sector is MIDCAP or SMALLCAP
    NIFTYNXT50   → when top sector is FACTOR_QUALITY or FACTOR_LOWVOL

  TIP: When in doubt, download NIFTY and BANKNIFTY every week. Add others
       only when your ETF system shows those sectors in the top 5.

STEP 2 — Run the script
────────────────────────
  Command:
    python options_trader.py

  The script will print its progress:
    [Regime]   reads holdings_log.json → BULL / PARTIAL / BEAR
    [Sectors]  reads etf_rankings.xlsx → top 5 investable ETFs + sectors
    [CSV]      scans folder for option-chain-ED-*.csv files
    [Signal]   for each top sector → checks IV rank → selects expiry + strike
    [Trade]    prints entry price, lots, stop-loss, target, time stop

INPUTS:
  - etf_rankings.xlsx           (your ETF system output — read only)
  - holdings_log.json           (your ETF system output — read only)
  - option-chain-ED-*.csv       (downloaded from NSE in Step 1)
  - iv_history.json             (auto-read if exists, created if not)

OUTPUTS:
  - options_trades.xlsx         → trade signals with all entry/exit details
  - iv_history.json             → updated with today's ATM IV per index
  - signals_log.json            → new signals appended (status = ACTIVE)

WHAT TO DO AFTER:
  Open options_trades.xlsx. Each green row is an actionable trade.
  Place orders in your broker terminal using:
    - Strike label  (e.g. NIFTY 23000 CE)
    - Expiry date
    - Lots recommended
  Note your actual fill price — it may differ slightly from the LTP shown.
  If your fill differs from LTP by more than 5%, check liquidity before entering.

IF REGIME = BEAR:
  No signals are generated. Do not trade. Close any open positions
  from prior weeks if the time stop or stop-loss has been hit.


