SCRIPT 2 — options_monitor.py
PURPOSE  : Daily MTM check — tells you whether to hold or exit each position
RUN WHEN : Every trading day — AFTER market close (3:35–3:45pm IST)
           Do NOT run during the last 30 mins of trading (3:00–3:30pm)
           LTPs are noisy intraday. Post-close prices are settled and reliable.
           Exception: exit intraday only if option is down 70%+ and the
           underlying is in clear freefall — that is not noise, that is a
           broken trade.
================================================================================

STEP 1 — Download fresh option chain CSVs for your OPEN positions only
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  URL  : https://www.nseindia.com/option-chain
  How  :
    a. For each index you have an open position in (e.g. NIFTY, BANKNIFTY):
    b. Select that index
    c. Select the SAME expiry as your open trade
    d. Download CSV and move to your options folder
       Old CSV files for the same index/expiry will be overwritten — that is fine.

  You only need CSVs for indices where you have open positions.
  You do not need to download all indices every day.

STEP 2 — Run the script
────────────────────────
  Command:
    python options_monitor.py

  The script reads all open (ACTIVE) positions from signals_log.json,
  looks up the current LTP from the fresh CSVs, and computes MTM.

INPUTS:
  - signals_log.json            (maintained by options_trader.py)
  - option-chain-ED-*.csv       (fresh download from Step 1)

OUTPUTS:
  - options_monitor.xlsx        → one row per open position with:
      Current LTP
      Unrealised P&L (₹ and %)
      Days to expiry
      Days to time stop
      ACTION column — one of:

        HOLD                        No exit triggered. Check again tomorrow.
        WATCH CLOSELY               Approaching stop-loss. Stay alert.
        CONSIDER EXITING            Near profit target (75%+ of the way there).
        PREPARE TO EXIT             Time stop is within 3 days.
        EXIT NOW — STOP-LOSS HIT    LTP at or below 50% of entry. Exit today.
        EXIT NOW — TARGET HIT       LTP at or above 2× entry. Book profit today.
        EXIT NOW — TIME STOP        Time stop date reached. Exit regardless of P&L.

WHAT TO DO AFTER:
  - If Action = HOLD           → no action needed. Re-check tomorrow.
  - If Action = EXIT NOW       → place exit order in broker immediately.
                                 Then run options_tradelog.py to record the exit.
  - If Action = WATCH / PREPARE → no action today but check again tomorrow.
                                  Do not average down or add to losing positions.

EXPIRY DAY RULE:
  Your time stop fires 2 trading days before expiry — so by expiry day
  you should have no open position in that contract.
  If you do (missed the time stop), exit in the first 30 minutes of trade
  (9:15–9:45am). Do not wait for the last hour — pinning risk is highest then.


================================================================================
SCRIPT 3 — options_tradelog.py
PURPOSE  : Records exits, updates P&L, regenerates trade_log.xlsx
RUN WHEN : Immediately after closing a position in your broker terminal
================================================================================

STEP 1 — Close the position in your broker first
──────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Place the exit order in your broker (Zerodha / Upstox etc.)
  Note the actual exit price (average fill price from your broker's trade book)

STEP 2 — Run the script
────────────────────────
  Command:
    python options_tradelog.py

  The script will show all open positions and ask you to close one or more.

  Interactive prompts:
    a. Enter the position number to close (shown in the list)
    b. Enter the exit LTP (your actual broker fill price)
    c. Select exit reason:
         [1] Stop-loss hit
         [2] Target hit
         [3] Time stop
         [4] Manual / other

  Repeat for each position being closed. Enter 0 when done.

INPUTS:
  - signals_log.json            (read + updated — ACTIVE → CLOSED)
  - trade_log.json              (read + updated — closed trade appended)

OUTPUTS:
  - signals_log.json            → position status updated to CLOSED
  - trade_log.json              → exit price, exit reason, P&L recorded
  - trade_log.xlsx              → regenerated with 3 sheets:

      Sheet 1: Trade Log
        Every closed trade — entry date, index, strike, expiry, entry LTP,
        exit LTP, move %, lots, total premium, P&L (₹), hold days, exit reason

      Sheet 2: P&L Summary
        Month-by-month — number of trades, winners, losers, win rate,
        gross P&L, avg win, avg loss, best trade, worst trade,
        total premium deployed, return on premium

      Sheet 3: Stats
        Overall win rate, profit factor, expectancy per trade,
        best/worst trade, max consecutive wins/losses,
        exit reason breakdown (how many stopped out vs target vs time stop),
        P&L by index


================================================================================
WEEKLY ROUTINE — FULL SEQUENCE
================================================================================

  MONDAY or FRIDAY (your chosen signal day)
  ──────────────────────────────────────────
  1. Run your ETF script first  →  refreshes etf_rankings.xlsx + holdings_log.json
  2. Check options_monitor.py   →  see if any open positions need closing first
  3. If exits needed            →  close in broker → run options_tradelog.py
  4. Download fresh CSVs        →  for indices matching your top ETF sectors
  5. Run options_trader.py      →  generates new signals for the week
  6. Place new orders           →  use options_trades.xlsx as your order sheet

  TUESDAY to THURSDAY (monitoring days)
  ──────────────────────────────────────
  1. After 3:30pm               →  download fresh CSVs for open positions only
  2. Run options_monitor.py     →  check Action column
  3. If EXIT NOW appears        →  close in broker → run options_tradelog.py
  4. Otherwise                  →  no action needed

  EXPIRY DAY (if you somehow still have an open position)
  ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  1. Exit at market open (9:15–9:45am) — do not wait
  2. Run options_tradelog.py to record the exit


